  "text": "A possible advantage of our formulation with two levels of quadratic interaction is that if adaptation is introduced at each stage (as for example, in taking the mean rather than the summed receptive field output) then such a neural system would be less likely to saturate. Adaptation is a well-known feature of striate cortical neurons [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
